00031 netsnmp_mib_handler *
00032 netsnmp_get_read_only_handler(void)
00033 {
00034     netsnmp_mib_handler *ret = NULL;
00035     
00036     ret = netsnmp_create_handler("read_only",
00037                                  netsnmp_read_only_helper);
00038     if (ret) {
00039         ret->flags |= MIB_HANDLER_AUTO_NEXT;
00040     }
00041     return ret;

00045 int
00046 netsnmp_read_only_helper(netsnmp_mib_handler *handler,
00047                          netsnmp_handler_registration *reginfo,
00048                          netsnmp_agent_request_info *reqinfo,
00049                          netsnmp_request_info *requests)
00050 {
00051 
00052     DEBUGMSGTL(("helper:read_only", "Got request\n"));
00053 
00054     switch (reqinfo->mode) {
00055 
00056     case MODE_SET_RESERVE1:
00057     case MODE_SET_RESERVE2:
00058     case MODE_SET_ACTION:
00059     case MODE_SET_COMMIT:
00060     case MODE_SET_FREE:
00061     case MODE_SET_UNDO:
00062         netsnmp_set_all_requests_error(reqinfo, requests,
00063                                        SNMP_ERR_NOTWRITABLE);
00064         return SNMP_ERR_NOTWRITABLE;
00065 
00066     case MODE_GET:
00067     case MODE_GETNEXT:
00068     case MODE_GETBULK:
00069         /* next handler called automatically - 'AUTO_NEXT' */
00070         return SNMP_ERR_NOERROR;
00071 
00072     default:
00073         netsnmp_set_all_requests_error(reqinfo, requests,
00074                                        SNMP_ERR_GENERR);
00075         return SNMP_ERR_GENERR;
00076     }
00077     netsnmp_set_all_requests_error(reqinfo, requests, SNMP_ERR_GENERR);
00078     return SNMP_ERR_GENERR;     /* should never get here */
00079 }
